Aux:TextAnnotations.Aux:document_text: • FASHION NEWS Teatum Jones win the Woolmark Prize 2016 British designer duo Teatum Jones took the 2016 edition of the Woolmark Prize, sponsored by the Australian body set up to regulate quality of wool products, winning 100,000 Australian dollars to support the development of their label. The duo behind Teatum Jones were the big winners at the 2016 International Woolmark Prize in the womenwear category, following the likes of Karl Lagerfeld and Yves Saint Laurent as previous winners of the award. With their expert use of woolen lace, double-sided wool and original use of color, the Wool Utopia-inspired collection won over the judges. In Ireland in 1892, Sister Agnès Morragh Bernard created the FoxFord Woolen Mills to weave rich luxurious wool blankets; a historical site visited by Teatum Jones duo during the development of their exclusive pieces. The collection displayed their modernization of the wool process with innovative geometric shapes and hand stitched embroidery on skirts and jackets. The London-based duo won 100,000 Australian dollars to develop their label and the support of an expert in the Australian wool industry. The capsule collection created for the contest will also be distributed in selected department stores worldwide, such as David Jones, Harvey Nichols and MyTheresa
